			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here is few aspects on how attack system will be implemented. I want to hear any suggestions about what can be wrong here or what is missing.
<br />

<br />
Factions &amp; alignment:
<br />

<br />
Alignment will consist of 3 components. Race alignment, deity alignment and faction alignment. Total alignment will be calculated as sum of those components and will be used to determine shop rates and mob behavior.  Each race will have alignment vs. any other race (even itself). The same applies for deity. Those 2 types of alignment will be uses to determine PC vs. NPC as well as NPC vs. NPC alignment. Alignment can be positive or negative. 
<br />

<br />
Faction alignment will be used only to determine PC vs. NPC or pet vs. NPC relationship. Every mob would have faction values assigned to it. They can be positive, negative or 0. NPC faction will be multiplied to the value of appropriate PC faction. All those values will be added together to calculate total faction alignment. Pet's faction will be the same as factions of it owner but race and deity factions will be their own. So if you have orc pet, it might be able to walk along other orcs but if you will take it to the city, guards might not like it and then they will get angry on you for taking such a beast into the city.
<br />

<br />
Your total alignment vs. NPC will determine how this NPC will con to you. Values around 0 will be indifferent. If alignment is large negative - it will attack you. If alignment is large positive - it will help you.
<br />

<br />
If you complete quest your faction changes will be the same as factions of this NPC. If you kill NPC, your faction changes will be opposite to the factions of this NPC. In order to complete quest your total alignment to this NPC should be greater then specific value.
<br />

<br />
Hate &amp; Damage list:
<br />

<br />
Every mob will hold 2 lists. Hate list and damage list. Hate list will be used to determine who will be attacked by the mob and damage list - who is responsible (and eventually will get credit / faction hit) for mob death. Hate list can be shared between more then one mob while damage list will be unique for every mob. Lets say if you attacking one orc and your friend attacking another and you are close to each other, then those 2 orcs will try to help each other and will really share one hate list and will attack together one person.
<br />

<br />
Lets say mob is attacking someone and is under control (pet or charmed). In damage list of attacked mob all damage made by pet will be recorded as it made by owner. Also owner will get some portion (how about 25%) of hate done by it's pet. Member of group will get let say 5% of the hate done by another member (if you are in the group, you should be responsible for actions of your partners).
<br />

<br />
If more then one person in mob hate list, it will attack the one who is on the top of this list. Poll: Should mob also take in account how easy target is to kill when choosing next target? Then mob will stick on this person unless another will do at get at least 10% more hate then current mob's target. This should prevent mob from switching between different targets too often. 
<br />

<br />
When mob is killed everyone in the damage list will get faction hit. Poll: do you think that everyone should get equal amount of faction hit or it should be prorated based on damage? Then person or group that made more damage to the mob will be given experience and right to loot. Group damage will be calculated and sum of damages made by members.
<br />

<br />
---------------------
<br />

