				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Simple example of another faction quirk:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">
<br />
Client&#58;&#58;onCastSpell&#40;&#41; &#123;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; // this could also be more general, ie&#58; if client is doing anything benevolent to the target...
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; if &#40;casting_spell.isBuff&#40;&#41; || casting_spell.isHeal&#40;&#41;&#41; &#123;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; target = getTarget&#40;&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; // and the target is engaged
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; if &#40;&#40;target != this&#41; &amp;&amp; target.isEngaged&#40;&#41;&#41; &#123;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; // get a list of mobs that the target currently has agro
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; hatelist = target.getAttachedHateLists&#40;&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; while &#40;hatelist.hasMore&#40;&#41;&#41; &#123;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; // add this client to the hatelists of the mobs his target currently has agro
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; mob = hatelist.getNext&#40;&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; mob.addToHateList&#40;this, CASTON_HATE_ADD_PERCENT&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &#125;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &#125;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &#125;
<br />
&#125;
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Im sure you could add logic to check if the client is in agro range or line of sight to make it more realistic.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
